    "actor": "https://uofa.net/morrison/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors appropriately scoped out at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40 Table 3. CFD model demonstrates sufficient predictive adequacy for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device. RH < 1 acceptance criterion met at all five operating points. The hemolysis power-law model parameterization referenced in the assessment methodology (https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ymeth.2024.03.003) provides updated Giersiepen-Wurzinger coefficients used for NIH calculation; this reference underpins the scalar stress integration approach applied throughout. Credibility sufficient to support regulatory submission at Medium assurance level.",
